1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,079
We are more than conquerors through Christ,

2
00:00:02,079 --> 00:00:05,079
and yes, we do have an enemy, and yes, they do.

3
00:00:05,079 --> 00:00:08,199
The enemy desires to devour us

4
00:00:08,199 --> 00:00:10,520
as we find in 1 Peter chapter number five,

5
00:00:10,520 --> 00:00:13,279
but I'm thankful for many verses of scripture

6
00:00:13,279 --> 00:00:14,239
that were coming to my mind

7
00:00:14,239 --> 00:00:17,040
even as we were singing that song this morning,

8
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:18,959
that greater is he that is in you

9
00:00:18,959 --> 00:00:21,120
than he that is in the world, amen?

10
00:00:21,120 --> 00:00:23,719
And submit yourselves therefore to God,

11
00:00:23,719 --> 00:00:28,719
resist the devil, and it says he will flee, amen?

12
00:00:28,799 --> 00:00:32,279
And we sang a couple of songs this morning

13
00:00:32,279 --> 00:00:34,040
by way of our congregational singing,

14
00:00:34,040 --> 00:00:36,319
all hail the power of Jesus' name,

15
00:00:36,319 --> 00:00:38,080
a mighty fortress is our God,

16
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:40,240
and if you looked at the bulletin this morning,

17
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:42,799
Proverbs 18, 10 is on the front,

18
00:00:42,799 --> 00:00:47,319
the name of the Lord is a strong tower, amen?

19
00:00:47,319 --> 00:00:51,360
And that bulletin was not selected because of the songs,

20
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:54,319
the songs were not selected because of the bulletin,

21
00:00:54,319 --> 00:00:57,979
and that's just how God orchestrated it for this morning,

22
00:00:58,580 --> 00:01:01,180
and I love it when God works that way,

23
00:01:01,180 --> 00:01:02,580
and someone asked me, they said,

24
00:01:02,580 --> 00:01:03,779
they looked at the front of the bulletin,

25
00:01:03,779 --> 00:01:05,620
and they said, I see the songs,

26
00:01:05,620 --> 00:01:07,059
was this bulletin picked for this?

27
00:01:07,059 --> 00:01:09,099
No, it's just how it worked, amen?

28
00:01:09,099 --> 00:01:11,260
We buy the bulletins, they come to us

29
00:01:11,260 --> 00:01:14,339
in a pack of 13 weeks at a time,

30
00:01:14,339 --> 00:01:18,739
so you get a quarterly bundle of these bulletins,

31
00:01:18,739 --> 00:01:20,180
and they get in a stack,

32
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:23,260
and Holly just goes week one, week two, week three,

33
00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:26,260
that's how it just works, and she has them that way,

34
00:01:26,260 --> 00:01:27,500
and then Dean picks the songs,

35
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:30,419
Dean never sees the bulletin until he comes to church, amen?

36
00:01:30,419 --> 00:01:32,220
And praise the Lord,

37
00:01:32,220 --> 00:01:35,099
and I'm thankful that we serve a great God, amen?

38
00:01:35,099 --> 00:01:38,120
And I mentioned about 1 Peter chapter number five,

39
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:41,379
where the Bible says that our enemy desires to devour us,

40
00:01:41,379 --> 00:01:44,419
but we read, and we often will quote verse number eight,

41
00:01:44,419 --> 00:01:45,419
but verse number nine says,

42
00:01:45,419 --> 00:01:49,139
whom resist steadfast in the faith,

43
00:01:49,139 --> 00:01:51,419
knowing that the same afflictions are accomplished

44
00:01:51,419 --> 00:01:54,099
in your brethren that are in the world.

45
00:01:54,099 --> 00:01:57,580
It ought to remind us to pray one for another, amen?

46
00:01:57,580 --> 00:02:00,459
In fact, as you read the truth in Ephesians,

47
00:02:00,459 --> 00:02:01,860
chapter number six,

48
00:02:01,860 --> 00:02:04,300
with regard to putting on the whole armor of God,

49
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:06,980
you read about the fact that we're engaged

50
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:09,259
in spiritual battle and all that's going on,

51
00:02:09,259 --> 00:02:11,399
and how we're to put on the whole armor of God,

52
00:02:11,399 --> 00:02:13,660
you get to the end after all the pieces of armor,

53
00:02:13,660 --> 00:02:16,320
and it talks about praying one for another,

54
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:19,020
and what a blessing to know that we have folks

55
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:21,860
that are praying for us as we're engaged

56
00:02:21,860 --> 00:02:23,220
in the spiritual battle.

57
00:02:23,220 --> 00:02:25,580
I believe it was Tozer that said it well.

58
00:02:25,580 --> 00:02:29,059
He said this, that the Christian life is best defined

59
00:02:29,059 --> 00:02:33,419
or described as a battleground, not a playground.

60
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:37,220
And I hope that you have discovered that to be the truth.

61
00:02:37,220 --> 00:02:39,820
It is a battlefield, a battleground,

62
00:02:39,820 --> 00:02:42,580
and I'm thankful to be on the winning side, amen?

63
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:44,240
James chapter number one this morning,

64
00:02:44,240 --> 00:02:45,339
if you have your Bible with you,

65
00:02:45,339 --> 00:02:47,100
James chapter number one,

66
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,020
and thankful for the word of God,

67
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:52,940
and what a blessing that God would give us His word

68
00:02:53,660 --> 00:02:55,899
and reveal to us the wonderful truth that He does.

69
00:02:55,899 --> 00:02:57,300
We find that as we've been studying

70
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:58,660
through the book of James last week,

71
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:00,300
we were in first John three,

72
00:03:00,300 --> 00:03:04,059
and dealing with the subject that Jesus loves even me.

73
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:05,899
This week, we're back to the book of James,

74
00:03:05,899 --> 00:03:09,979
our book study for the calendar year of 2026.

75
00:03:09,979 --> 00:03:13,860
And we are looking here, doers of the word is our theme,

76
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,839
and thankful for the book of James.

77
00:03:15,839 --> 00:03:19,339
James, as we mentioned in the beginning of our study here,

78
00:03:19,339 --> 00:03:22,100
immediately addresses the subject of trials

79
00:03:22,139 --> 00:03:23,820
as he opens the letter.

80
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,559
We've said this multiple times

81
00:03:25,559 --> 00:03:27,059
with regard to the book of James.

82
00:03:27,059 --> 00:03:29,860
It's a book that is very practical in nature,

83
00:03:29,860 --> 00:03:33,100
and the importance of spiritual maturity

84
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:35,580
and taking what we believe to be true

85
00:03:35,580 --> 00:03:36,779
and then practicing it.

86
00:03:36,779 --> 00:03:39,740
How do we apply God's word in our lives

87
00:03:39,740 --> 00:03:41,160
that we'd be doers of the word?

88
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:43,139
He deals with the subject of trials,

89
00:03:43,139 --> 00:03:46,339
and we discover this that all of us have faced

90
00:03:46,339 --> 00:03:48,139
or will face trials.

91
00:03:48,139 --> 00:03:50,839
It's something that as human beings, we deal with,

92
00:03:50,839 --> 00:03:54,720
we face trials as believers, we face trials,

93
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:58,080
but we have a different perspective when facing trials

94
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:01,839
because we understand that God has given to us his word

95
00:04:01,839 --> 00:04:03,899
and he's revealed truth to us

96
00:04:03,899 --> 00:04:08,259
that helps us as we face the trials that we face in life.

97
00:04:08,259 --> 00:04:11,100
And so throughout the first section of this book,

98
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:14,440
we've learned several things with regard to trials.

99
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:17,160
Number one, we've learned that we ought to expect trials.

100
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,640
Trials are gonna come in your life and in my life.

101
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:22,679
And you say, pastor, I'm in the midst of one right now.

102
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:26,940
I understand, and we understand the scriptures teach us

103
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:28,720
that we're to expect trials.

104
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,980
We understand that trials come in various ways

105
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:33,640
and they come at various times.

106
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:37,000
Rarely is the trial ever come the same way,

107
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:41,320
and they come in variety of ways and a variety of times.

108
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:44,220
And you might find that at times a trial will come

109
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,839
and you might say something like this,

110
00:04:45,839 --> 00:04:47,559
this is not the time for this.

111
00:04:47,559 --> 00:04:48,519
You ever felt that way?

112
00:04:48,519 --> 00:04:51,200
And you say, man, I don't have time for this right now.

113
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:53,959
And we can sometimes have that perspective,

114
00:04:53,959 --> 00:04:57,559
but we understand that God's given to us these truths

115
00:04:57,559 --> 00:04:59,760
that will help us as we face trials.

116
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,160
What about this truth?

117
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:04,440
God has a purpose in the trial.

118
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,059
Oh, that'll help us, amen.

119
00:05:06,059 --> 00:05:08,660
We're not just going through the trial for no good reason.

120
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:09,640
We're going through the trial

121
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:12,760
because God has a purpose in that trial.

122
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:15,160
At times, the purpose is that he is going

123
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:17,239
to demonstrate his power.

124
00:05:17,239 --> 00:05:20,279
He's going to reveal something to us about his person,

125
00:05:20,279 --> 00:05:22,239
and that should cause us to rejoice.

126
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:24,559
At other times, and sometimes both working

127
00:05:24,559 --> 00:05:28,380
in the same trial, it's to develop us as his people,

128
00:05:28,380 --> 00:05:31,799
to grow us, to help us to trust him more

129
00:05:31,799 --> 00:05:35,420
and to lean on him more, to believe him more.

130
00:05:35,420 --> 00:05:39,720
And we also have learned that we need God's wisdom

131
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:42,440
when we're experiencing trials, amen.

132
00:05:42,440 --> 00:05:44,200
We need the wisdom of God.

133
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,799
And I'm thankful that God has promised

134
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,839
to give wisdom to those who ask.

135
00:05:49,839 --> 00:05:51,799
As we come to verse number 12 this morning,

136
00:05:51,799 --> 00:05:55,399
it's interesting because the passage with regard to trials

137
00:05:55,399 --> 00:05:59,359
kind of concludes here in verse number 12.

138
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:04,320
And I'll say this, with a sermon on the mount kind of a tone

139
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:08,079
and it's regarding the individual that endures.

140
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:10,799
Now, remember, if you think about the sermon on the mount,

141
00:06:10,799 --> 00:06:13,239
blessed is, and you read about all of those things.

142
00:06:13,239 --> 00:06:15,799
And we come to verse number 12 of James one,

143
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:16,799
and the Bible says,

144
00:06:16,799 --> 00:06:20,920
blessed is the man that endureth temptation.

145
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:24,880
For when he is tried, he shall receive the crown of life,

146
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:29,100
which the Lord hath promised to them that love him.

147
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:30,799
As we look at verses two through 12,

148
00:06:30,799 --> 00:06:33,760
we understand that the word temptation is used

149
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,000
dealing with trials.

150
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,640
And we find that in verses 13 through 15,

151
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:42,239
the word tempted is used repeatedly and dealing with,

152
00:06:42,239 --> 00:06:43,920
and you understand the context,

153
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:46,559
a different type of temptation

154
00:06:46,559 --> 00:06:49,839
than the temptation that we read of in verses two through 12

155
00:06:49,839 --> 00:06:52,279
the temptation that we deal with in verses two through 12

156
00:06:52,279 --> 00:06:55,279
are temptations as we talked about these trials

157
00:06:55,279 --> 00:06:58,640
and understanding that they come, they're not sinful.

158
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:02,399
They are to reveal to us God's power

159
00:07:02,399 --> 00:07:04,600
and God's purpose and his plan.

160
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:07,839
And we find that they're to develop us as his people.

161
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:10,720
In verses 13 through 15, as we'll study next week,

162
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:13,880
that's dealing more with sinful aspect.

163
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,600
And the context helps us to understand that.

164
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,880
And so as we look here in verse number 12,

165
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:22,679
it's important that we know that James is not saying

166
00:07:22,679 --> 00:07:27,160
that a sinner is saved by enduring trials.

167
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,880
That's not what he's saying.

168
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:32,040
What he's saying is that a believer

169
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:36,200
who endures trials will be rewarded.

170
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:38,000
There's a great difference.

171
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,239
It's not that, oh man, I've endured all of this

172
00:07:41,239 --> 00:07:42,640
and I've gone through all of this.

173
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,079
And sometimes you talk to somebody,

174
00:07:44,079 --> 00:07:45,079
are you gonna go to heaven when we die?

175
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:46,160
Well, let me tell you what happened.

176
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:48,079
And they had this thing going on in their life

177
00:07:48,079 --> 00:07:49,440
and they made it through.

178
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,640
And so therefore, man, I'm gonna, no, no, no.

179
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,440
Salvation is through Jesus Christ.

180
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:56,119
There's a moment in which you recognized you were a sinner.

181
00:07:56,119 --> 00:07:57,200
He's the only savior.

182
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,440
And you trust that Christ is your savior.

183
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:01,359
And you were born again.

184
00:08:01,359 --> 00:08:04,959
And we understand that James is not suggesting

185
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:08,040
you're teaching here that a sinner is saved

186
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:12,399
by enduring trials, but rather as a believer

187
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:15,399
that endures trials, we will be rewarded.

188
00:08:15,399 --> 00:08:16,799
I've titled the message simply,

189
00:08:16,799 --> 00:08:19,920
as you see in the bulletin today, Enduring Trials.

190
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:21,320
As you're looking at verse number 12,

191
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:24,320
I want you to note first of all with me the conduct.

192
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,799
Note the conduct of the individual

193
00:08:26,799 --> 00:08:29,260
who is mentioned here in our verse of scripture.

194
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:30,820
The Bible says, blessed is the man

195
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:32,640
that endureth temptation.

196
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:35,119
For when he has tried, he shall receive the crown of life,

197
00:08:35,119 --> 00:08:38,320
which the Lord hath promised to them that love him.

198
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,440
We notice two things about the conduct

199
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:43,320
of the individual that is mentioned in verse number 12.

200
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:46,400
Now understand, in verse number two,

201
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,719
that James, as he starts this section

202
00:08:48,719 --> 00:08:50,960
and now is going to conclude the section,

203
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:53,840
he starts it by saying, my brethren.

204
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:56,880
And understanding that he's writing to believers.

205
00:08:56,880 --> 00:09:00,359
And he says, my brethren, count it all joy

206
00:09:00,359 --> 00:09:03,679
when you fall into divers temptations.

207
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:05,479
And he's going to give all of the truth

208
00:09:05,479 --> 00:09:08,979
that I just briefly summarized by way of introduction,

209
00:09:08,979 --> 00:09:11,380
those principles that we've learned

210
00:09:11,380 --> 00:09:13,859
as we've studied through this portion of scripture.

211
00:09:13,859 --> 00:09:16,539
And now he comes to the concluding statement

212
00:09:16,539 --> 00:09:19,419
in verse number 12 and wrapping up the section.

213
00:09:19,419 --> 00:09:22,700
And he reveals to us the conduct of the individual

214
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:26,280
that yes, has gone through trials, but has endured.

215
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:29,940
We read that it says, blessed is the man that endureth.

216
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:32,020
And I want you to focus just a moment

217
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:34,820
as you think about the conduct of this individual

218
00:09:34,820 --> 00:09:36,619
on the one that endureth.

219
00:09:36,619 --> 00:09:38,580
The word means to remain.

220
00:09:38,979 --> 00:09:40,099
It means to abide.

221
00:09:40,099 --> 00:09:42,380
It means to persevere.

222
00:09:42,380 --> 00:09:45,099
It really carries with it this idea

223
00:09:45,099 --> 00:09:48,380
of no retreat and no fleeing.

224
00:09:48,380 --> 00:09:52,099
You know, sometimes what happens in the midst of a trial,

225
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:56,340
people get the pressure and they retreat.

226
00:09:56,340 --> 00:09:57,580
They give up.

227
00:09:57,580 --> 00:09:59,080
They throw in the towel.

228
00:09:59,080 --> 00:09:59,919
They say, what's.

229
00:09:59,919 --> 00:10:02,299
What's it worth?

230
00:10:02,299 --> 00:10:04,999
And they get discouraged and all of those things happen,

231
00:10:04,999 --> 00:10:08,179
but we find here when we note the conduct of the individual

232
00:10:08,179 --> 00:10:10,379
that is given to us in verse number 12,

233
00:10:10,379 --> 00:10:11,219
the Bible says,

234
00:10:11,219 --> 00:10:14,579
blessed is the man that endureth temptation,

235
00:10:14,579 --> 00:10:16,099
that the trial comes,

236
00:10:16,099 --> 00:10:19,859
but there's this aspect, this conduct of enduring,

237
00:10:19,859 --> 00:10:21,679
understanding that I'm gonna remain,

238
00:10:21,679 --> 00:10:23,659
I'm gonna keep my eyes on Jesus.

239
00:10:23,659 --> 00:10:27,139
We're reminded of the truth in Hebrews chapter number 12,

240
00:10:27,139 --> 00:10:31,279
of looking unto Jesus, the author and finisher of our faith

241
00:10:31,279 --> 00:10:35,279
and understanding that he has a plan and he has a purpose

242
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:39,399
and I'm going to endure through the trial by God's grace

243
00:10:39,399 --> 00:10:41,079
and with God's help.

244
00:10:41,079 --> 00:10:45,319
It's not that in myself, I just have this ability to endure.

245
00:10:45,319 --> 00:10:47,919
No, it's through God's working in my life

246
00:10:47,919 --> 00:10:50,519
and understanding the biblical principles

247
00:10:50,519 --> 00:10:53,279
that God has revealed to us.

248
00:10:53,279 --> 00:10:54,679
It really carries with it,

249
00:10:54,679 --> 00:10:58,299
the idea to hold fast to your faith in Christ,

250
00:10:58,299 --> 00:11:00,939
even in the midst of trials.

251
00:11:02,259 --> 00:11:04,199
There are times if you'd be honest

252
00:11:04,199 --> 00:11:05,819
and we're not gonna have anyone

253
00:11:05,819 --> 00:11:07,979
share publicly a testimony,

254
00:11:07,979 --> 00:11:11,099
but if you'd be honest and you'd evaluate your own life,

255
00:11:11,099 --> 00:11:13,719
there's probably been at some point in your Christian life

256
00:11:13,719 --> 00:11:14,859
that you were enduring it,

257
00:11:14,859 --> 00:11:18,339
you were going through a trial and it was heavy

258
00:11:18,339 --> 00:11:19,899
and it was difficult

259
00:11:19,899 --> 00:11:23,539
and maybe the thought crossed your mind,

260
00:11:23,539 --> 00:11:24,719
is it even worth it?

261
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:29,079
Maybe the thought of quitting crossed your mind.

262
00:11:29,079 --> 00:11:31,079
Listen, I know people that have quit

263
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:34,039
and I'm sure you do as well.

264
00:11:34,879 --> 00:11:37,239
People that in the midst of a trial,

265
00:11:37,239 --> 00:11:40,159
that remember the trial was not designed,

266
00:11:40,159 --> 00:11:42,319
we focused on this a couple of weeks ago,

267
00:11:42,319 --> 00:11:45,439
the trial is not designed to defeat us

268
00:11:45,439 --> 00:11:47,759
or to destroy us or to discourage us.

269
00:11:47,759 --> 00:11:51,759
No, the trial is designed to enable us to grow

270
00:11:51,779 --> 00:11:54,339
and to flourish and to be used of the Lord,

271
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:58,299
but at times because of the human nature that we have,

272
00:11:58,299 --> 00:12:02,939
that we face those trials and it can be so overwhelming

273
00:12:02,939 --> 00:12:05,219
that we're ready to just quit.

274
00:12:05,219 --> 00:12:06,419
But here the Bible says,

275
00:12:06,419 --> 00:12:10,619
blessed is the man that endureth temptation.

276
00:12:10,619 --> 00:12:13,459
It's a sad thing when I see individuals,

277
00:12:13,459 --> 00:12:17,779
believers that are discouraged and on the brink of quitting.

278
00:12:17,779 --> 00:12:19,819
I know pastors that have quit

279
00:12:19,839 --> 00:12:21,999
and I'm sure that you do as well.

280
00:12:21,999 --> 00:12:24,359
They just got so overwhelmed in the work of the ministry

281
00:12:24,359 --> 00:12:27,799
and so overwhelmed with problems and whatever it might be

282
00:12:27,799 --> 00:12:29,879
and they just got discouraged.

283
00:12:29,879 --> 00:12:31,799
Every time I go to a pastor's meeting,

284
00:12:32,719 --> 00:12:35,239
I don't go to them every single month,

285
00:12:35,239 --> 00:12:36,639
but there is a pastor's meeting

286
00:12:36,639 --> 00:12:39,119
that I try to hit as often as I can.

287
00:12:39,119 --> 00:12:41,319
It's held once a month

288
00:12:41,319 --> 00:12:43,759
and I go as often as I can possibly go.

289
00:12:43,759 --> 00:12:46,879
But as I pray, as I'm traveling to those meetings,

290
00:12:46,879 --> 00:12:47,999
I always pray this way,

291
00:12:47,999 --> 00:12:51,019
Lord, there's probably somebody that's gonna be there

292
00:12:51,019 --> 00:12:52,899
that's ready to quit.

293
00:12:52,899 --> 00:12:55,859
God, would you help me to be able to be an encouragement

294
00:12:55,859 --> 00:12:57,339
and a blessing to that individual?

295
00:12:57,339 --> 00:12:59,579
Would you help me to be able to know what to say,

296
00:12:59,579 --> 00:13:02,379
to try to keep them in the fight?

297
00:13:02,379 --> 00:13:05,339
Listen, the devil wants you to get discouraged and quit.

298
00:13:05,339 --> 00:13:06,659
The devil wants you to drop out.

299
00:13:06,659 --> 00:13:08,939
He wants you to become a casualty.

300
00:13:08,939 --> 00:13:10,099
That's what the enemy wants.

301
00:13:10,099 --> 00:13:11,299
But in the midst of the trial,

302
00:13:11,299 --> 00:13:13,099
we find the conduct of the individual

303
00:13:13,099 --> 00:13:14,779
that's mentioned in verse number 12

304
00:13:14,779 --> 00:13:16,579
that James is writing here.

305
00:13:16,579 --> 00:13:19,979
He says, blessed is the man that endureth.

306
00:13:20,879 --> 00:13:23,399
And we find here not only the conduct

307
00:13:23,399 --> 00:13:25,319
of the one that endures to persevere,

308
00:13:25,319 --> 00:13:29,079
to remain, to abide, to stay close to God.

309
00:13:29,079 --> 00:13:30,079
You know, in the midst of the trial,

310
00:13:30,079 --> 00:13:32,159
that's when you need God the most.

311
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:32,999
Amen?

312
00:13:32,999 --> 00:13:33,819
You know what happens?

313
00:13:33,819 --> 00:13:35,479
I see it so often, what happens,

314
00:13:35,479 --> 00:13:36,939
somebody's in the midst of a trial.

315
00:13:36,939 --> 00:13:38,239
I mean, the most difficult trial

316
00:13:38,239 --> 00:13:40,719
maybe they've ever endured and they've had in their lives

317
00:13:40,719 --> 00:13:43,759
and they do this, they come apart from church.

318
00:13:43,759 --> 00:13:45,319
They come apart from God.

319
00:13:45,459 --> 00:13:46,619
They don't come to church.

320
00:13:46,619 --> 00:13:47,459
Why?

321
00:13:47,459 --> 00:13:50,279
Because they're so burdened and they're so heavy

322
00:13:50,279 --> 00:13:51,739
and they feel like I can't.

323
00:13:51,739 --> 00:13:54,539
And listen, that's when you need church the most.

324
00:13:55,399 --> 00:13:56,899
They don't read their Bible.

325
00:13:56,899 --> 00:13:57,739
Why?

326
00:13:57,739 --> 00:13:59,419
Because they're in the midst of this trial

327
00:13:59,419 --> 00:14:01,819
and they're overwhelmed and they're heavy.

328
00:14:01,819 --> 00:14:04,479
No, that's when you need the Bible the most.

329
00:14:04,479 --> 00:14:05,319
Amen?

330
00:14:06,379 --> 00:14:09,459
And what happens is sometimes we take exactly

331
00:14:09,459 --> 00:14:13,199
the opposite approach of what we should be taking,

332
00:14:13,199 --> 00:14:14,899
that I need more.

333
00:14:15,439 --> 00:14:16,959
I need to be in God's presence.

334
00:14:16,959 --> 00:14:18,319
I need to have more from God.

335
00:14:18,319 --> 00:14:21,079
Listen, there's something that God can do

336
00:14:21,079 --> 00:14:23,159
in the midst of the trial in your life

337
00:14:23,159 --> 00:14:26,239
through the fellowship with the brethren,

338
00:14:26,239 --> 00:14:28,079
through the preaching of the word.

339
00:14:28,079 --> 00:14:29,239
You read the Bible.

340
00:14:29,239 --> 00:14:32,159
Listen, there's times when your heart is overwhelmed

341
00:14:32,159 --> 00:14:35,219
and maybe your mind is just not where it ought to be,

342
00:14:35,219 --> 00:14:36,799
but you keep reading the Bible

343
00:14:36,799 --> 00:14:37,959
and you keep reading the Bible

344
00:14:37,959 --> 00:14:40,679
and you keep going to church and God will help you.

345
00:14:42,299 --> 00:14:43,759
We need it.

346
00:14:43,759 --> 00:14:46,099
We don't need to come apart and say,

347
00:14:46,099 --> 00:14:47,979
you just don't know how bad it is.

348
00:14:47,979 --> 00:14:51,979
No one may know how bad it is, but God does.

349
00:14:53,379 --> 00:14:54,859
And can I tell you something that's,

350
00:14:54,859 --> 00:14:57,499
and I know it might not make somebody feel good,

351
00:14:57,499 --> 00:14:59,339
but let me just be honest with you.

352
00:14:59,339 --> 00:15:01,459
The reality is it doesn't really matter

353
00:15:01,459 --> 00:15:03,459
if anyone understands how hard it is.

354
00:15:04,419 --> 00:15:05,499
It doesn't matter.

355
00:15:05,499 --> 00:15:08,299
What really matters is that God knows.

356
00:15:08,299 --> 00:15:09,499
You know why that matters?

357
00:15:09,499 --> 00:15:13,459
Because if for some reason I can understand

358
00:15:13,459 --> 00:15:15,959
exactly the heartache that you have,

359
00:15:15,959 --> 00:15:17,959
I can't really do a whole lot about it.

360
00:15:19,199 --> 00:15:20,039
Amen?

361
00:15:21,559 --> 00:15:26,559
So even if I could fully understand the severity

362
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:29,759
of the difficulty that you're facing,

363
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:33,679
I can't really help like God can.

364
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:35,879
Amen?

365
00:15:36,759 --> 00:15:37,919
And sometimes we can get overwhelmed.

366
00:15:37,919 --> 00:15:39,839
Just nobody understands.

367
00:15:39,839 --> 00:15:41,679
No, no, God understands.

368
00:15:41,699 --> 00:15:44,539
And he's the only one that matters.

369
00:15:44,539 --> 00:15:45,659
Amen?

370
00:15:45,659 --> 00:15:47,219
And we need to understand that.

371
00:15:47,219 --> 00:15:49,979
We need to have that concept in our minds

372
00:15:49,979 --> 00:15:52,419
to realize that God understands

373
00:15:52,419 --> 00:15:56,699
and that God is able to help us to endure

374
00:15:56,699 --> 00:15:58,819
through the temptation, through the trial.

375
00:15:58,819 --> 00:16:01,579
Notice at the end of the verse, the Bible says this,

376
00:16:01,579 --> 00:16:02,859
which the Lord hath promised.

377
00:16:02,859 --> 00:16:05,899
Notice what it says, to them that love him.

378
00:16:05,899 --> 00:16:08,499
We not only notice the conduct of this individual

379
00:16:08,499 --> 00:16:10,219
that's mentioned in verse number 12,

380
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:11,359
that they're enduring,

381
00:16:11,359 --> 00:16:13,519
but we understand that the scriptures say here

382
00:16:13,519 --> 00:16:15,439
that they love God.

383
00:16:15,439 --> 00:16:16,999
Oh, I'm so thankful.

384
00:16:16,999 --> 00:16:19,499
Last week, we focused on the entire message

385
00:16:19,499 --> 00:16:22,559
of the truth that God loves me.

386
00:16:22,559 --> 00:16:25,159
In fact, I titled the message last Sunday morning,

387
00:16:25,159 --> 00:16:26,879
Jesus Loves Even Me.

388
00:16:26,879 --> 00:16:31,459
What a blessing to understand the love of God

389
00:16:31,459 --> 00:16:35,419
and to have Paul praise for the believers in Ephesus

390
00:16:35,419 --> 00:16:38,239
that they would comprehend God's love,

391
00:16:38,239 --> 00:16:40,039
that they would truly understand

392
00:16:40,859 --> 00:16:43,179
and it's sad when you think about the church at Ephesus

393
00:16:43,179 --> 00:16:45,859
for the indictment against them in the book of Revelation

394
00:16:45,859 --> 00:16:46,699
when the letter is written

395
00:16:46,699 --> 00:16:49,579
is that they left their first love.

396
00:16:49,579 --> 00:16:52,059
And here we find that the scriptures tell us

397
00:16:52,059 --> 00:16:54,559
of this one that is mentioned in verse number 12

398
00:16:54,559 --> 00:16:57,239
that not only is their conduct one of enduring,

399
00:16:57,239 --> 00:17:01,259
but we find that their conduct is one that they love God.

400
00:17:01,259 --> 00:17:02,859
What does it mean to love God?

401
00:17:02,859 --> 00:17:07,099
Understand 1 John plainly teaches us that we love him

402
00:17:07,099 --> 00:17:08,979
because he first loved us.

403
00:17:08,979 --> 00:17:11,759
And we understand that the Bible continues to teach us

404
00:17:11,759 --> 00:17:14,399
in the book of 1 John that when we love him,

405
00:17:14,399 --> 00:17:16,279
we keep his commandments.

406
00:17:16,279 --> 00:17:19,319
There is evidence, proof positive evidence

407
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:23,919
that God gives us in his word, whether or not we love God.

408
00:17:23,919 --> 00:17:28,519
Anyone can run around and have a t-shirt, a hat,

409
00:17:28,519 --> 00:17:32,539
a bracelet or whatever that says, I love Jesus.

410
00:17:33,759 --> 00:17:35,519
You can buy them, you can get them.

411
00:17:36,339 --> 00:17:38,259
But the scriptures give us evidence

412
00:17:38,259 --> 00:17:40,939
of what it means to love Jesus, to love God.

413
00:17:41,779 --> 00:17:44,379
And we find that as we understand this individual

414
00:17:44,379 --> 00:17:46,619
and we begin to comprehend the truth

415
00:17:46,619 --> 00:17:49,379
that the Bible says to them that love him.

416
00:17:49,379 --> 00:17:52,779
I asked the question this morning, do we really love God?

417
00:17:52,779 --> 00:17:56,979
Now think about this, if I understand God's love for me

418
00:17:57,979 --> 00:18:02,539
and in response to God's love for me, I love God.

419
00:18:02,539 --> 00:18:04,739
And I understand within the context

420
00:18:04,759 --> 00:18:07,319
of what we're looking at here in James chapter number one,

421
00:18:07,319 --> 00:18:09,399
that I'm going through a trial.

422
00:18:09,399 --> 00:18:12,059
I'm, as it says, I've fallen into,

423
00:18:12,059 --> 00:18:14,679
according to verse number two, this divers temptations.

424
00:18:14,679 --> 00:18:16,779
I'm facing a trial in my life,

425
00:18:16,779 --> 00:18:19,399
but as I'm facing the trial in my life,

426
00:18:19,399 --> 00:18:22,319
I'm reminded of a very important truth

427
00:18:22,319 --> 00:18:24,359
and that is God's love for me.

428
00:18:26,919 --> 00:18:29,239
Paul asked the question in Romans chapter number eight,

429
00:18:29,239 --> 00:18:32,440
what can separate us from the love of God?

430
00:18:32,440 --> 00:18:34,000
We won't take the time to look there,

431
00:18:34,059 --> 00:18:35,539
but at the end of Romans chapter number eight,

432
00:18:35,539 --> 00:18:37,859
the scriptures go through a whole list of things

433
00:18:37,859 --> 00:18:40,419
and then tell us that no, there's nothing

434
00:18:40,419 --> 00:18:42,219
that can separate us from the love of God.

435
00:18:42,219 --> 00:18:44,579
Listen, the trial that you're enduring,

436
00:18:44,579 --> 00:18:46,019
the trial that you're facing,

437
00:18:46,019 --> 00:18:49,260
the trial that's got you upside down and overwhelmed.

438
00:18:49,260 --> 00:18:51,719
Let me remind you that God loves you,

439
00:18:51,719 --> 00:18:53,899
but when you understand God's love for you,

440
00:18:53,899 --> 00:18:55,700
then you love him.

441
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:58,619
And when I love God and I have that desire

442
00:18:58,619 --> 00:19:01,260
to keep his commandments and I love him

443
00:19:01,260 --> 00:19:04,000
in the best possible way that I could love him,

444
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,239
then I don't wanna give up,

445
00:19:06,239 --> 00:19:07,639
I don't wanna throw in the towel,

446
00:19:07,639 --> 00:19:09,919
I don't wanna miss what God has for me, why?

447
00:19:09,919 --> 00:19:11,599
Because I love God.

448
00:19:13,239 --> 00:19:15,440
And I believe the truth of verse number 12,

449
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:18,119
though it's dealing with the trials contextually,

450
00:19:18,119 --> 00:19:21,919
verses two through 12, dealing with the trials that we face,

451
00:19:21,919 --> 00:19:24,760
verse 13 through 15, dealing with the temptations,

452
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,399
the sinful aspect.

453
00:19:26,399 --> 00:19:28,639
Can I tell you that the truth of verse number 12,

454
00:19:28,639 --> 00:19:32,739
really the last part with regard to them that love him,

455
00:19:32,739 --> 00:19:36,700
them that love God, carries with it a dual application.

456
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:40,380
Not only does it help me to endure the trials that I face,

457
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:42,359
but can I say this and really a preview

458
00:19:42,359 --> 00:19:43,779
to next week's message?

459
00:19:43,779 --> 00:19:47,839
When I love God, it's gonna keep me from sin.

460
00:19:49,419 --> 00:19:50,919
Because I love God more.

461
00:19:52,339 --> 00:19:53,619
I love God more.

462
00:19:55,619 --> 00:19:58,219
And we see, as we'll look at the temptation

463
00:19:58,219 --> 00:20:00,959
that contextually is dealt with in verse.

464
00:20:00,959 --> 00:20:03,479
verses 13 through 15 with the subject of sin.

465
00:20:03,479 --> 00:20:04,319
How do we know that?

466
00:20:04,319 --> 00:20:06,759
Because it says that it bringeth forth sin

467
00:20:06,759 --> 00:20:08,679
and sin what is finished bringeth forth death.

468
00:20:08,679 --> 00:20:11,839
And so we understand that's a different type of temptation

469
00:20:11,839 --> 00:20:14,559
than what is dealt with in verses two through 12.

470
00:20:14,559 --> 00:20:17,839
And we find that the context helps us to understand that.

471
00:20:17,839 --> 00:20:20,479
But I wanna remind you this morning

472
00:20:20,479 --> 00:20:22,719
that as we look at the trials that we face,

473
00:20:22,719 --> 00:20:25,539
I mean, just living life and going through storms

474
00:20:25,539 --> 00:20:27,439
and difficulties and trials,

475
00:20:27,439 --> 00:20:30,639
we must remember that God loves us,

476
00:20:30,639 --> 00:20:34,099
but we must love God, we must love Him.

477
00:20:37,079 --> 00:20:39,859
And if I love Him, not only can I endure

478
00:20:39,859 --> 00:20:42,659
through the trial of life, but it will keep me from sin.

479
00:20:44,399 --> 00:20:45,459
It'll keep me from sin.

480
00:20:45,459 --> 00:20:46,699
I use this illustration,

481
00:20:46,699 --> 00:20:48,579
I'll probably use it again next week.

482
00:20:48,579 --> 00:20:51,779
But the reality is that we live in a world

483
00:20:51,779 --> 00:20:54,259
that obviously sin is just all around us

484
00:20:54,259 --> 00:20:55,819
and it bombards us.

485
00:20:55,819 --> 00:21:00,579
But when sin enters and there's some temptation to sin,

486
00:21:01,419 --> 00:21:05,039
we have a choice, amen, we have a choice.

487
00:21:06,159 --> 00:21:07,839
And if you love God more,

488
00:21:09,899 --> 00:21:12,439
if your love for God is what it ought to be,

489
00:21:12,439 --> 00:21:15,639
it'll keep us from that sin.

490
00:21:15,639 --> 00:21:18,219
It'll help us to endure through the trials,

491
00:21:18,219 --> 00:21:20,439
but also keep us from the sin

492
00:21:20,439 --> 00:21:22,679
that temptations can bring.

493
00:21:22,679 --> 00:21:23,859
So we note the conduct,

494
00:21:23,859 --> 00:21:26,679
the individual that is mentioned here in verse number 12

495
00:21:26,679 --> 00:21:29,859
is an individual that endures.

496
00:21:29,859 --> 00:21:31,799
Listen, it's not that, have you ever had this idea?

497
00:21:31,799 --> 00:21:34,379
Well, they just never have any problems.

498
00:21:34,379 --> 00:21:36,719
You know, maybe somebody, you know,

499
00:21:36,719 --> 00:21:39,159
I've had people say this to me, all right?

500
00:21:39,159 --> 00:21:41,119
Counseling situations, I've had people say,

501
00:21:41,119 --> 00:21:42,239
well, pastor, you just don't understand

502
00:21:42,239 --> 00:21:44,079
because you don't have any problems.

503
00:21:44,079 --> 00:21:47,199
I've had people say that to me.

504
00:21:49,959 --> 00:21:50,839
Sometimes I don't have any problems,

505
00:21:50,839 --> 00:21:52,399
I just don't share my problems.

506
00:21:52,539 --> 00:21:55,379
I just don't share my problems.

507
00:21:58,179 --> 00:22:00,979
We all have trials, we all have storms.

508
00:22:02,419 --> 00:22:05,219
They all come in different ways and at different times.

509
00:22:07,419 --> 00:22:09,259
And we have to come to the place

510
00:22:09,259 --> 00:22:10,659
where it's not that we look at somebody and say,

511
00:22:10,659 --> 00:22:12,259
well, look at how well,

512
00:22:12,259 --> 00:22:14,259
they just must never have a bad day.

513
00:22:14,259 --> 00:22:15,859
They just never have a problem.

514
00:22:15,859 --> 00:22:18,299
Just the enemy must not know their address.

515
00:22:18,299 --> 00:22:21,499
I mean, they just never have a trial, no.

516
00:22:23,259 --> 00:22:25,759
It's that they have a perspective

517
00:22:25,759 --> 00:22:28,499
that's a biblical, godly perspective.

